headline: The Bull Case For Capital One (COF) Could Change Following Trump’s Proposed 10% Card APR Cap - Learn Why
summary: In recent days, Capital One Financial has come under pressure after President Trump proposed a one-year 10% cap on credit card interest rates, raising fresh regulatory uncertainty for the entire card industry. Analysts now see the political spotlight on credit costs as a material risk factor for card issuers, even if the proposal is ultimately unlikely to take effect because of legal and legislative hurdles.
